data.title: National Beverage Corp. (NASDAQ: FIZZ) starts stock buyback program; company cites strong fundamentals and geopolitical challenges.
data.description: National Beverage Corp. (NASDAQ: FIZZ) has initiated open market purchases of its common stock and plans to provide additional information at a later date. The acquisitions were conducted in accordance with the Company’s existing share buyback initiative. Despite challenges such as the government shutdown, SNAP program funding, and tariffs, the company maintains its robust financial position and strong cash flow generation. Further details about the stock purchases will be disclosed in due course.

data.title: iQmetrix reveals new Interconnected Commerce Retail Suite: iQ Storefront, iQ Hub, and iQ Pay at SummitX 2025 in Carlsbad.
data.description: In Carlsbad, California, iQmetrix introduced its latest Interconnected Commerce Retail Suite at SummitX 2025 on October 20. This innovative suite includes iQ Storefront, iQ Hub, and iQ Pay, designed for telecom retail. The live product demonstrations showcased the advancements, signifying a significant step in iQmetrix's goal to transform how telecom retailers engage in digital-first strategies and AI-infused operations.

data.title: Mastercard's Q3 net revenues reached $8.60 billion, up 17% Y/Y. Adjusted EPS rose 13% to $4.38, surpassing estimates. Visa and American Express also reported strong performance. Resilient consumer spending evident despite inflation fears.
data.description: Financial services company Mastercard (NYSE: MA) released its fiscal third-quarter results, showcasing quarterly net revenues of $8.60 billion, a 17% increase year-over-year and a 15% surge on a neutral currency basis. This surpassed analyst predictions of $8.53 billion. Adjusted EPS also saw a remarkable rise of 13% year-over-year to $4.38, exceeding the anticipated $4.32 by analysts. Similarly, Visa Inc (NYSE: V) reported positive quarterly results, reflecting strong consumer spending trends. American Express Co (NYSE: AXP) also noted record quarterly revenue, driven by its affluent customer base. Mastercard's payment network net revenue experienced a 13% year-over-year increase, both in reported numbers and on a currency-neutral basis, fueled by growth in gross dollar volume (up 9% year-over-year) and cross-border transactions. For a detailed report, visit Benzinga.com.

data.title: 24% of enterprises installed ChatGPT Atlas, posing security risks due to unresolved challenges like prompt injection.
data.description: Cyberhaven Labs has underscored potential security risks within corporate environments due to unresolved issues like prompt injection, as indicated by new research on AI-powered browsers. The research, based in MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif., was shared on Oct. 30, 2025, by Cyberhaven, revealing how these challenges could lead to data leakage and manipulation. This emphasizes the importance of addressing such vulnerabilities to safeguard sensitive information.

data.title: Swinerton appoints Jason Bone as Director, National Design-Build to lead company's strategy and innovation.
data.description: Swinerton Incorporated based in Concord, California has appointed Jason Bone as the Director of National Design-Build on October 30, 2025. In this role, Bone will oversee setting national benchmarks for client-focused innovation and driving Swinerton's design-build strategy. This move underscores Swinerton's commitment to enhancing its design-build capabilities under Bone's leadership.

data.title: SDI Presence appoints Brian L. Payne as Senior Delivery Executive for Managed Services, SLED-West, expanding services for clients.
data.description: A recent appointment has bolstered the managed services leadership team of SDI Presence LLC, a prominent IT consultancy and managed services provider based in Chicago. The addition aims to enhance delivery excellence for state and local government clients. The appointment was made public on October 30, 2025. This move reflects the firm's commitment to expanding its capabilities in serving government clients and further solidifying its position in the market.

data.title: Global automotive repair and service market to hit $2.4 trillion by 2034, growing at 7.6% CAGR due to rising vehicle age.
data.description: In Portland, Oregon on October 30, 2025, it was reported that a significant factor contributing to the growth of the automotive repair and service sector is the rising average age of vehicles on a global scale. This trend has led to a higher demand for routine maintenance, part substitutions, and diagnostic services as car owners opt to retain their vehicles for longer periods. The need for these services has surged as a result of consumers choosing to hold onto their cars.

data.title: Inventor from Miami Gardens develops PAW PRINTS emergency communication device for service dogs.
data.description: In Pittsburgh on October 30, 2025, an inventor from Miami Gardens, Florida expressed their motivation to innovate a wireless emergency communication device for service dogs. The invention, named PAW PRINTS, aims to aid in locating the service dog or calling for assistance during emergencies. The device is designed to serve this purpose effectively.

data.title: Assent Inc. acknowledges manufacturers for sustainable supply chain efforts in Achieve Awards 2025.
data.description: Assent Inc., a company based in Ottawa, recognized several businesses in the recent Assent Achieve Awards ceremony. The honored companies were applauded for their efforts in enhancing transparency, sustainability, and Environmental, Social, and Governance (ESG) practices within their supply chains. The awards ceremony, held on October 30, 2025, celebrated companies that have made significant impacts in these areas. Assent Inc., known as the leader in supply chain sustainability management, commended the recipients for their commitment to driving positive change.

data.title: Deere & Company highlights FFA as top youth ag organization in US, preparing students for the future.
data.description: The country's leading youth agriculture organization is equipping students for the future in Moline, Illinois, as of October 30, 2025. The FFA stands as the primary school-centered youth development group in the U.S., fostering leadership, personal development, and career achievements.

data.title: CPSC warns consumers to stop using ILIKER pajama sets due to risk of serious injury or death. View warnings at www.cpsc.gov.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) issued a warning regarding ILIKER Pajama Sets, urging consumers to cease usage immediately. The CPSC emphasized the risk of serious injury or death associated with these products. For more information on product safety warnings and recalls, consumers are advised to visit www.cpsc.gov.

data.title: European Research Centres Directory 2025 offers access to all research development activities in Europe across 19 subjects.
data.description: A directory titled "European Research Centres Directory 2025" has recently been included in the offerings of ResearchAndMarkets.com. This directory aims to offer extensive access to various research and development activities across Europe, encompassing governmental, university, independent, nonprofit, and commercial entities. The listings in the European Research Centers Directory are categorized into 19 sections based on subjects such as Agriculture & Food, Archaeology & History, Astronomy, and Biology. This comprehensive resource serves as a valuable source for those seeking information on the research landscape in Europe.

data.title: Consilio appoints Tricia Kinney as Chief Legal Officer, leading global legal functions. Andy Macdonald is CEO.
data.description: In Washington, Consilio, a prominent global provider of legal technology solutions and enterprise legal services, has named Tricia Kinney as Chief Legal Officer. Kinney will report to CEO Andy Macdonald and will oversee global legal, compliance, and governance operations as the company expands through the Aurora digital enterprise platform. Her appointment follows the departure of predecessor Mike Flanagan, who will be moving on to other responsibilities within the organization.
